newsitem.title: CANADA: Toronto-Dominion Bank cuts prime to 5.25.
newsitem.headline: Toronto-Dominion Bank cuts prime to 5.25.

text.p: Toronto-Dominion Bank said on Wednesday it cut its prime lending rate to 5.25 percent from 5.50 percent, effective on Thursday.
The move followed a Bank of Canada rate cut of 25 basis points to 3.75 percent.
It matched identical moves by Bank of Montreal and Bank of Nova Scotia.
Canada's major banks last changed their prime lending rates on October 3, when they lowered them to 5.50 percent from 5.75 percent.
The prime rate is the rate charged by banks on loans to their best customers.
